## 🏛️ Platform Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    User["👤 Normal User"] -->|browse + request| FE["Next.js Frontend"]
    UA["🏫 University Admin"] -->|manage own CMS| FE
    SA["🛡️ Super Admin"] -->|full control| FE
    FE -->|HTTPS REST| BE["FastAPI Backend"]
    BE -->|read / write| DB["Firebase Firestore"]
    BE -->|vector search| FAISS["FAISS Embedding Index"]
    BE -->|LLM fallback| GEMINI["Gemini AI"]
    BE -->|emails| SMTP["Gmail SMTP"]
    DB -->|approved data only| FAISS
```

---

## 👥 Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

### Three Distinct Roles

| Role | Login | Permissions |
|---|---|---|
| **Normal User (student)** | Email + OTP | Browse universities, use chatbot, request new university |
| **University Admin** | Email + Password | Manage CMS for their assigned university only. All changes → pending |
| **Super Admin** | Email + Password (reset required) | Full platform control. Approve/reject all changes |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> All role checks are enforced **server-side** in [app/dependencies.py](file:///c:/Users/sujit/arvion-ai/backend/app/dependencies.py). University Admins cannot access another university's data even by intercepting API calls — the backend verifies their UUID's assigned `university_id` on every request.

---

## 🚦 Complete Approval Workflow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant UA as University Admin
    participant BE as Backend API
    participant DB as Firestore
    participant SA as Super Admin
    participant RAG as Chatbot (RAG)

    UA->>BE: Create/Edit/Delete CMS entry
    BE->>DB: Save with status: pending
    SA->>BE: GET /cms/super-admin/pending
    BE->>SA: Returns all pending entries
    SA->>BE: POST /cms/super-admin/approve/{id}
    BE->>DB: Update status → approved
    BE->>BE: Generate embedding vector
    BE->>RAG: Cache invalidated → AI learns new data
    Note over RAG: AI now answers from approved content
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Soft Delete Workflow:** When a University Admin deletes an entry, it becomes `pending_delete`. The Super Admin must review and approve the deletion. The AI never sees deleted or pending content.

---

## 🤖 AI Chatbot Architecture

### How It Works
1. User types a question in the university chat page
2. Backend calls **RAGService** for that specific university
3. FAISS searches the **approved** knowledge base for semantically similar content
4. If confidence ≥ 75% → returns knowledge base answer
5. If confidence < 75% → falls back to **Gemini AI** with context
6. Response is logged to [query_logs](file:///c:/Users/sujit/arvion-ai/backend/app/routers/admin.py#71-84) for admin analytics

### Data Sources (Both Feed the AI)
| Source | Collection | Filter |
|---|---|---|
| Knowledge Files (CSV/Excel) | `university_knowledge` | `verified: true` |
| Dynamic CMS Entries | `university_cms` | `status: approved` AND `is_deleted: false` |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The chatbot only reads `status: approved` CMS entries. Pending, rejected, or deleted content is never exposed to users or the AI.

